    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks @caybro \r\n\r\nI've taken a look and this does seem to be the only place where we don't have the close cross on a dialog/modal. I agree, from the user's perspective, this is something that they would expect to see and having it elsewhere in the app reinforces this expectation. \r\n\r\n@John-44 do you recall if there were any specific design decisions made around omitting the X here? It certainly makes more room for the top right controls but I wonder if we could reinstate it if we used a vertical pipe to segregate it out from those controls? It wouldn't be in the exact same location as in the other dialogs but given this is a fairly custom designed dialog it might be ok?\r\n\r\n<img width=\"672\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/215099486-af576e78-45b0-4b82-9f6f-b693e0d2f09f.png\">\r\n",
